<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: sans-serif;
            padding: 16px;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #333;
            background-color: #fff;
        }
        body.amoled {
            background-color: #000000 !important;
            color: #E6E1E5 !important;
        }
        h1 { color: #EF4444; }
        h2 { margin-top: 24px; color: #333; }
        a { color: #2563EB; }

        @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
            body {
                background-color: #1C1B1F; /* Standard Material 3 dark surface color */
                color: #E6E1E5;
            }
            h1 { color: #FFB4AB; }
            h2 { color: #E6E1E5; }
            a { color: #D0BCFF; }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Last updated: February 8, 2026</p>

    <h2>1. Data Collection</h2>
    <p>Drink Tracker is designed to work offline. We do not collect, store, or transmit any personally identifiable data to our servers.</p>

    <h2>2. Local Data</h2>
    <p>All data related to drinks, history, and friends list is stored locally on your device. If you clear the app data or uninstall it, this data will be lost.</p>

    <h2>3. Advertising (AdMob)</h2>
    <p>We use Google AdMob to display advertisements. AdMob may collect and use technical data (such as the device advertising ID) to provide relevant ads. For more information, please refer to <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

    <h2>4. Required Permissions</h2>
    <p>The app requires Internet access only to load advertisements and to update the widget (if present).</p>

    <h2>5. Contacts</h2>
    <p>For any privacy-related questions, you can contact us within the app through the official support channels.</p>
</body>
</html>
